`PRICING` is keyed on base model names like `"claude-opus-4-7"`, but `response.model` from the Anthropic API returns versioned IDs like `"claude-opus-4-7-20251101"`. The exact-key lookup `PRICING[model]` will always be `undefined`, so `estimateCost` always returns `null` and cost tracking is silently broken.

Fix:
```js
const key = Object.keys(PRICING).find(k => model.startsWith(k));
const p = key ? PRICING[key] : null;
```
